<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-2">
    <img src="{$baseUrl}/public/osuImages/editorialTeam/hess.jpg" alt="" class="portrait">
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10">
    <h2>Dr. Jim Hess</h2>
    <p>
      Dr. Jim Hess currently serves as the Chairman and SNB Professor of the OSU School of Healthcare Administration.  Dr. Hess previously served as the Chief Operating Officer and Vice President of the Oklahoma State University Center for Health Sciences and Chief Executive Officer of the OSU Physicians Practice Group.  Dr. Hess also serves as a Riata Faculty Fellow in the School of Entrepreneurship.  Dr. Hess’s research in the disciplines of emotional intelligence, problem solving, innovation and conflict management have been published in a number of academic publications.  In addition, he provides consulting services to organizations in the areas of healthcare economics, leadership and organizational development, executive mentorship and conflict management.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-2">
    <img src="{$baseUrl}/public/osuImages/editorialTeam/murray.jpg" alt="" class="portrait">
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10">
    <h2>Dr. Kelly Murray</h2>
    <p>
      Dr. Kelly Murray, PharmD, BCACP graduated from the University of Oklahoma College of Pharmacy in 2007. She is a Clinical Assistant Professor of Clinical Pharmacy at the OSU College of Osteopathic Medicine, Emergency Medicine department. She is also the Emergency Department Clinical Pharmacist at OSU Medical Center. She received her board certification in ambulatory care pharmacy in 2011. Her research interests include medication errors, communication skills, and adverse drug prevention, and migraine.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-2">
    <img src="{$baseUrl}/public/osuImages/editorialTeam/veit.jpg" alt="" class="portrait">
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10">
    <h2>Dr. Kaleb Veit</h2>
    <p>
      Dr. Veit graduated from Oklahoma State University College of Osteopathic Medicine in 2012. He completed his residency in internal medicine at Oklahoma State University Medical Center in January 2016. He recently served as a clinical assistant professor of internal medicine for the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center in Tulsa from July 2016-June 2017. His clinical and research interests include evidence-based medicine, neurology, hematology, cardiovascular medicine, and pulmonary/critical care medicine. Dr. Veit is a life-long OSU fan. He is active in his faith, enjoys sports and coffee, and is getting married in December.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

